&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">While these symptoms could either be mild or severe, and they can appear anywhere from a few hours to 10 days after coming into contact with the irritant or allergen. A contact dermatitis rash is a non-communicable disease and does not spread to anyone else.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If youâ€™re of that opinion that, you have come in contact with an allergen or irritant, wash the affected area with soap and water immediately. Symptoms of contact dermatitis include:Â </span>

